Package imagingbook.lib.ij.overlay

Class ShapeOverlayAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • imagingbook.lib.ij.overlay.ShapeOverlayAdapter
  • public class ShapeOverlayAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
    This is an adapter for ImageJ's Overlay class to ease the insertion of AWT Shape elements. Shapes are only geometric descriptions but have no stroke width, color etc. attached. These are supplied by ShapeOverlayAdapter's state when insertion is done with addShape(Shape) or explicitly specified by calling addShape(Shape, ColoredStroke). When a shape is inserted into the associated overlay it is converted to an ImageJ ShapeRoi instance whose stroke/fill properties are set. See also ColoredStroke.
    Version:
    2021/10/26
